<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14073">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b>Check out the Digital Resource Guide for the Citizenship in
      the World merit badge
      <a
        href="https://www.scouting.org/skills/merit-badges/digital-resource-guides/citizenship-in-the-world/"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      for information and helpful resources to engage your learning and assist
      you along on your merit badge journey!<br />
      The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Citizenship%20in%20the%20World.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-6331">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Explain what citizenship in the world means to you and what you think it
      takes to be a good world citizen. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/gfZgtP7VGGg" target="_blank"
        >What Does It Mean To Be a Global Citizen? (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/IH8AmE6mV9k" target="_blank"
        >What Is Global Citizenship? (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-6332">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Explain how one becomes a citizen in the United States, and explain the
      rights, duties, and obligations of U.S. citizenship. Discuss the
      similarities and differences between the rights, duties, and obligations
      of U.S. citizens and the citizens of two other countries. <br /><i
        >Resources:</i
      >
      <a href="https://youtu.be/JVXQvJvfuGw" target="_blank"
        >What Is Citizenship? (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/yYEfLm5dLMQ" target="_blank"
        >A Guide to the Bill of Rights (video)</a
      ><br /><a
        href="https://youtu.be/AyY01lTZZMk?si=zznVuQnQry5uJirc"
        target="_blank"
        >What Are the Rights and Responsibilities of Citizens</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/TYtsc07PiLQ" target="_blank"
        >Duties and Obligations of Being a Filipino Citizen (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/fxnVVftKrhI" target="_blank"
        >Fundamental Duties as a Citizen of India (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-6303">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-6303 mb-requirement-id-6304">
        (a) Pick a current world event. In relation to this current event,
        discuss with your counselor how a country's national interest and its
        relationship with other countries might affect areas such as its
        security, its economy, its values, and the health of its citizens.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/geCF1K76nEs" target="_blank"
          >National Interest in International Relations (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-6303 mb-requirement-id-6305">
        (b) Select a foreign country and discuss with your counselor how its
        geography, natural resources, and climate influence its economy and its
        global partnerships with other countries. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://geolutins.com/the-impact-of-geography-on-the-global-economy"
          target="_blank"
          >The Impact of Geography on the Global Economy (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://resourcetrade.earth" target="_blank"
          >resourcetrade.earth (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://oec.world/en" target="_blank"
          >The Observatory of Economic Complexity (OEC) (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.usgs.gov/educational-resources/usgs-geospatial-data-sources"
          target="_blank"
          >USGS Geospatial Data Sources (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-6306">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Do TWO of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-6306 mb-requirement-id-6315">
        (a) Explain international law and how it differs from national law.
        Explain the role of international law and how international law can be
        used as a tool for conflict resolution. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/-VSD2d35ijI" target="_blank"
          >National Law vs International Law (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/C9m6IQX87G4" target="_blank"
          >What Are Treaties and How Do They Work? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/ePV1J48cGYI" target="_blank"
          >Why Do We Need International Law? (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-6306 mb-requirement-id-6316">
        (b) Using resources such as major daily newspapers, the internet (with
        your parent or guardian's permission), and news magazines, observe a
        current issue that involves international trade, foreign exchange,
        balance of payments, tariffs, and free trade. Explain what you have
        learned. Include in your discussion an explanation of why countries must
        cooperate in order for world trade and global competition to thrive.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/1hY8OhTH6ag" target="_blank"
          >Free Trade Agreement (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/UGLPiyeQVxU" target="_blank"
          >What Is Free Trade? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/QrAwFXiwPnQ" target="_blank"
          >Balance of Payments &amp; Foreign Reserves Explained (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/98U_Vb8rQfs" target="_blank"
          >What Is Currency? Exchange Rates (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/_tmPnH-JkNg" target="_blank"
          >Free Trade and Protectionism (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-6306 mb-requirement-id-6307">
        (c) Select TWO of the following organizations and describe their role in
        the world.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-6307 mb-requirement-id-6308">
        (1) United Nations and United Nations Children's Fund (UNICEF) <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Ttoad811t88" target="_blank"
          >What Is the United Nations? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/cx0QyKoyU6A" target="_blank"
          >What Is UNICEF? (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-6307 mb-requirement-id-6309">
        (2) International Court of Justice (The World Court) <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/kJKgYZfeMkE" target="_blank"
          >What Is the International Court of Justice? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.icj-cij.org/home" target="_blank"
          >International Court of Justice (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-6307 mb-requirement-id-6333">
        (3) International Criminal Police Organization (Interpol) <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/nQ1iFMlw0KI" target="_blank"
          >What Is The INTERPOL? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.interpol.int/" target="_blank"
          >INTERPOL (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-6307 mb-requirement-id-6310">
        (4) World Organization of the Scout Movement <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/EEyM_ChN1yM" target="_blank"
          >World Organization Scout Movement (WOSM) (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.scout.org/" target="_blank"
          >World Scouting (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-6307 mb-requirement-id-6311">
        (5) World Health Organization (WHO) <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/qhvx5oxbYn0" target="_blank"
          >The WHO Explained (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.who.int/" target="_blank"
          >World Health Organization (WHO) (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-6307 mb-requirement-id-6312">
        (6) Amnesty International <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/xLIndY8JuNk" target="_blank"
          >What Does Amnesty International Do? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.amnesty.org/en/" target="_blank"
          >Amnesty International (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-6307 mb-requirement-id-6313">
        (7) International Federation of Red Cross and Red Crescent Societies
        (IFRC) <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/ReE835-d8vk" target="_blank"
          >Together We Are the International Federation of Red Cross and Red
          Crescent Societies (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.ifrc.org/" target="_blank">IFRC (website)</a>
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-6307 mb-requirement-id-6314">
        (8) Cooperative for American Relief Everywhere (CARE) <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/MfRlqpKo_t0" target="_blank"
          >CARE International (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.care.org/" target="_blank"
          >CARE International (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-6307 mb-requirement-id-6334">
        (9) European Union <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/8G1cds52Ko0" target="_blank"
          >What Is the European Union? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://european-union.europa.eu/index_en" target="_blank"
          >European Union (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-6317">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-6317 mb-requirement-id-6318">
        (a) Discuss the differences between constitutional and nonconstitutional
        governments. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://difbetween.com/constitutional-vs-nonconstitutional-governments.p15758/"
          target="_blank"
          >Constitutional vs Nonconstitutional Governments (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-6317 mb-requirement-id-6319">
        (b) Name at least five different types of governments currently in power
        in the world. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://worldostats.com/politics/government-type-by-country/"
          target="_blank"
          >Types of Government Around the World: Country Comparison (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-6317 mb-requirement-id-6320">
        (c) Show on a world map countries that use each of these five different
        forms of government. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://worldmapblank.com/pages/free-maps" target="_blank"
          >World Maps (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://freeworldmaps.net/political.html" target="_blank"
          >Political World Maps (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-6321">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-6321 mb-requirement-id-6322">
        (a) Explain how a government is represented abroad and how the United
        States government is accredited to international organizations. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/3kDp6mT1ioE" target="_blank"
          >What Is the State Department? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/bOs5H39dlRA" target="_blank"
          >What Are Embassies, Consulates, and Missions? (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-6321 mb-requirement-id-6323">
        (b) Describe the roles of the following in the conduct of foreign
        relations: ambassador, consul, Bureau of Global Public Affairs, United
        States and Foreign Commercial Service. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/LdKFN1g62PM" target="_blank"
          >What Is Diplomacy and How Does It Work? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/XJAeLeBW6l8" target="_blank"
          >Ambassadors: An Overview of the Role and Responsibilities of
          Diplomatic Representatives (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/pRRsmcWtpt4" target="_blank"
          >Export With the US Commercial Service (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://diplomacy.state.gov/what-is-a-u-s-consulate/"
          target="_blank"
          >What Is a U.S. Consulate? (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-6321 mb-requirement-id-6324">
        (c) Explain the purpose of a passport and visa for international travel.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/gDOXgWtCQxY" target="_blank"
          >Becoming a U.S. Citizen: An Overview of the Naturalization Process
          (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtube.com/shorts/Pmu0NXzj-Fo" target="_blank"
          >What Is the Process for Obtaining a Permanent Residency in the US?
          (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/R_OhIkzkF2Y" target="_blank"
          >Visa vs Passport—Know The Important Differences! (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-6325">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 7. </span>
      Do TWO of the following (with your parent or guardian's permission) and
      share with your counselor what you have learned:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-6325 mb-requirement-id-6326">
        (a) Visit the website of the U.S. State Department. Learn more about an
        issue you find interesting that is discussed on this website. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/jJH1d0hG-RQ" target="_blank"
          >What Does the State Department Do? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.usa.gov/" target="_blank">USA.gov (website)</a>
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-6325 mb-requirement-id-6327">
        (b) Visit the website of an international news organization or foreign
        government, OR examine a foreign newspaper available at your local
        library, bookstore, or newsstand. Find a news story about a human right
        realized in the United States that is not recognized in another country.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/ew993Wdc0zo" target="_blank"
          >Human Rights (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.reuters.com/" target="_blank">Reuters (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/section/world" target="_blank"
          >The New York Times World News (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-6325 mb-requirement-id-6328">
        (c) Visit with a student or Scout from another country and discuss the
        typical values, holidays, ethnic foods, and traditions practiced or
        enjoyed there.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-6325 mb-requirement-id-6329">
        (d) Attend or participate in a World Organization of the Scouting
        Movement (WOSM) event such as the World Scout Jamboree, World Scout
        Moot, World Scout Congress, Jamboree Over The Air, or Jamboree Over The
        Internet. Attendance at a national or regional Jamboree sponsored by a
        WOSM-National Scout Organization is also allowed. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/reg45_nepRo" target="_blank"
          >A Recap on the 25th World Scout Jamboree (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.scouting.org/international/international-adventure/world-scout-jamboree-stories-once-in-a-lifetime-or-lifechanging/"
          target="_blank"
          >Attending a World Scout Jamboree—Once in a Lifetime or Lifechanging?
          (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://vimeo.com/1157342063/39dc53d4ba?fl=ip&amp;fe=ec"
          target="_blank"
          >What Is the World Jamboree (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.scouting.org/international/resources/"
          target="_blank"
          >International Scouting Tools and Resources (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.scout.org/jamboree-live" target="_blank"
          >World Scout Jamboree—Live Shows (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.scout.org/news/ultimate-scout-packing-list"
          target="_blank"
          >The Ultimate Scout Camp Packing List (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://wsj2019.us/scholarships/" target="_blank"
          >World Scout Jamboree Scholarship Information (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-6325 mb-requirement-id-6330">
        (e) Participate in or attend an international event in your area, such
        as an ethnic festival, concert, or play. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/" target="_blank"
          >Eventbrite (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://allevents.in/" target="_blank">Allevents (website)</a>
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
</div>
